The NGO launched #SaveSyria following scenes of devastation in Aleppo and is using the money to assist refugees of the war. JOHANNESBURG - Non-governmental organisation Operation SA says South Africans have donated over R13.9 million in just under two months to assist with humanitarian efforts in Syria.The organisation launched the initiative called #SaveSyria last December following scenes of devastation in Aleppo and is using the money to assist refugees and orphans of the war.Operation SA activist Yusuf Abramjee says it s heartening to see South Africans from all sectors of society digging deep into their pockets and making a difference. We saw the devastation, hardship, pain and the suffering at Syrian borders and South Africans have shown, in the true spirit of Ubuntu, what a difference we can make. We thank them for donating so generously. 